Brent Crude Oil’s Premium to WTI Benchmark Widens for Third Day

-- B y   N i d a a   B a k h s h
-- 
2011-08-02T09:13:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-02/brent-crude-oil-s-premium-to-wti-benchmark-widens-for-third-day.html
The premium of North Sea Brent crude,
 Europe ’s benchmark, to the U.S. West Texas Intermediate grade
widened for a third day.  The spread between the two front-month contracts increased
to $22.16 a barrel as of 10:09 a.m. London time from $21.92
yesterday, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nidaa Bakhsh in London at 
 nbakhsh@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at   sev@bloomberg.net  